pageContext.claim: “I think you see that even last night where people charged the border, tried to get through but they couldn't because we have a wall up. And -- but tear gas was flying and a lot of things were happening and I guess for the most part you've seen it. It's very sad.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump says a wall prevented people who "charged the border" from getting through, but leaves out that many U.S. border officials were at this location and threw the tear gas he mentioned.
